      "action": "journal-upsert",
      "id": "v47-cohort",
      "strategy_id": "v47-cohort",
      "cohort_label": "v47",
      "hypothesis": "v47 cohort - test dropping the dead-weight filters from v25-bot-excl-climbing. /counterfactual reports that 3 of v25's 5 filters are 'dead weight' (Δret pp at or near zero when removed): top5<=30% (+0.04pp), vel<200 (0pp), age>=60s (+0.16pp). Only dd>-25% (-1.26pp = pulls weight) and climbing_t30_t45 (-1.12pp) actually contribute to per-trade return. These dead-weight filters are flagged not because they're conceptually useless, but because they're too LOOSE to reject much: top5 rejects ~1% of rows, vel<200 rejects ~0%, age>=60s rejects ~3%. The cohort tests whether removing them improves trade coverage without hurting per-trade quality. Five variants: drop top5 only, drop vel only, drop age only, drop all three (lean = only dd + climbing), and lean + acc_t30>-8 (stacks the v40-acc-gate winning filter, which has been the only NEW filter to improve things in months). Success = drop3 >= v25-base AND n_trades > v25-base (more coverage, same edge). If the lean variant matches v25-base on drop3, the three dead-weight filters are confirmed redundant and can be dropped from the canonical bot-excl-climbing template.",
      "prediction": {
        "target_net_sol": 0,
        "target_n": 100,
        "target_days": 21,
        "kill_criterion": "cohort-level - see individual variants"
      },
      "status": "OPEN"
    },
